FG-331 — “Raised • Ruled • Relief” Ribbon (Header Cue)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Put a three-word ribbon at the top of sections: Raised (where), Ruled (what), Relief (ask).
	•	📖 Lesson Content: One line per section header: Raised (Doc/pin), Ruled (quote or “not reached”), Relief (two-line order). It orients skim-readers immediately.
	•	📝 Assignment: Add a header ribbon to two argument sections.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Raised: Dkt 14:3 • Ruled: ‘did not reach harm’ (Dkt 18:2) • Relief: remand 21d for (a–d).”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: A tiny compass at the top of every turn.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A slim colored banner with three short labels and pins.

⸻

FG-332 — Docket Title Stack (Caption • Title • Metadata)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Fix all three layers so intake/search align: caption line, document title, PDF Title metadata.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: One-page notice listing current vs. correct for each layer; attach corrected p.1; ask clerk to suppress the mis-link.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft a 7-line “title stack” correction for your last filing.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Correct ‘Letter’ → ‘Motion for Preliminary Injunction’; PDF Title set; first page attached; suppress prior link.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Search works when names do.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: Three stacked labels snapping into alignment.

⸻

FG-333 — Master Crosswalk.xlsx (Issue → Pin → Tab → Relief)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Keep one spreadsheet that maps issue → proof → order text.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Columns: Issue • Dkt/Ex/Tr pin • Appx Tab p.# • Relief line; one row per proof; version it (v1.2) and cite once in the brief.
	•	📝 Assignment: Build a 12-row master crosswalk; export as PDF for the appendix.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Harm gap — Dkt 18:2 — Tab 3 p.2 — remand 21d for (a–d).”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: One sheet turns pages into a pathway.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A compact grid with an “Export PDF” tag and a fingerprint.

⸻

FG-334 — Parentheticals ≤10 Words (Holdings, Not Stories)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: TOA parentheticals should state the holding in ≤10 words.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Cut motive/adjectives; keep rule line only; mirror the holding in SoR; align relief to that rule.
	•	📝 Assignment: Trim four parentheticals to ≤10-word holdings.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Winter — factor-tied findings required (holding).”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Small holdings travel; stories stumble.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A citation tile with a tiny 10-word counter.

⸻

FG-335 — OA Yes/No Card (Two Doors in 20 Words)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Prepare a palm card that states the yes door and the safe door.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Line 1 (Yes): “Reverse (wrong test) (Dkt/Tab).” Line 2 (Safe): “Limited remand 21d for (a–d).” Repeat those words to close.
	•	📝 Assignment: Write your two-line yes/no card and print it.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Yes: reverse (wrong test; Dkt 18:2; Tab 3 p.2). Safe: remand 21d for harm findings.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Two doors cover the room.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A pocket card split “YES / SAFE” with pins.

⸻

FG-336 — Rehearing Grounds Micro-Checklist (Line • Pin • Door)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Panel rehearing wins on one misread line + one pin + one narrow door.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Checklist: Misread line (quote) • Contrary pin • Small remedy (clarify/limited remand). No new facts; ≤700–1300 words by rule.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft a 6-line rehearing skeleton with one misread and one fix.
	•	✅ Model Response: “p.12 n.3 ‘reached harm’ → ‘not reached’ (Dkt 18:2); clarify or remand 21d.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: One fixable sentence > ten grievances.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A magnifier over a single footnote, arrowing to a tiny order.

⸻

FG-337 — Costs & Fees Split Note (FRAP 39 vs. §1988)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Put costs and fees in the right court on one page.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Table: Item • Rule • Forum (FRAP 39 in appellate; 39(e)/§1988 below); attach receipts and lodestar sheet; propose coordinated orders.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft a 6-row split note with an order line.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Tax FRAP 39 here; 39(e)/§1988 below by stip; orders coordinated.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: One map ends duplicate fights.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: Two ledgers pointing to a single stamp “coordinated.”

⸻

FG-338 — Seal Revisit Schedule (Sunset • Log • Hash)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Every seal gets a revisit date and a line-by-line log.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Motion: redaction log + 90-day revisit; public/under-seal PDFs both hashed; propose automatic lift except lines listed.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft a 7-line revisit motion with a 6-row log.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Unseal all but Tab 7 p.3 l.4–17 (PII); revisit 90d; SHA-256 listed.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Sunsets build trust and lighten dockets.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: Black bars lifting off a page with a small “90d” tag.

⸻

FG-339 — Posture Snapshot Box (Statute • Clock • Copies)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Paste a small triangle box into every draft—page one and OA.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Statute (1291/1292/§705), Clock (Rule 58/FR/FRAP math), Copies (judgment/order tabs). Delete if redundant in final.
	•	📝 Assignment: Create a 3-line posture box you can paste anywhere.
	•	✅ Model Response: “§1291; Rule 58 08/15 → NOA 08/19; judgment/PI at Tabs 1–2.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Comfort earns minutes you didn’t have.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A small triangle badge with three labels.

⸻

FG-340 — Release Cadence (v-Tag • Note • Mirrors)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Version every outward artifact like software.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: On release: add v-tag to footer/filename; post 90-word note with hashes; update mirrors (same hash); commit Master_Index.csv row.
	•	📝 Assignment: Ship a v-tagged artifact and write its release note today.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Release v6 — Petition index posted; SHA-256 …; mirrors M-1/M-2 same hash.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Rhythm → trust → reuse.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A small “v6” badge on a document tile with a fingerprint.